definition.value: Any of the ducts that are part of a male reproductive system.
A sheet of somatopleure that grows upward over the embryo and eventually meets in the midline enclosing the embryo, eventually giving rise to the amnion and chorion[Kardong].
Anatomical structure embedded in or located in the integument that is part of the integumental system. Examples: hair, follicles, skin glands, claws, nails, feathers.

The thin bilaminar membrane derived from the prechordal plate that is devoid of mesoderm and formed by the apposition of the stomodeal ectoderm with the foregut endoderm; after the embryonic head fold has evolved it lies at the caudal limit of the stomodeum, forming a septum between the primitive mouth and pharynx; the membrane eventually disappears, and thus a communication is established between the mouth and the future pharynx.
An anatomical junctions that overlaps the mouth and foregut.

The auditory pit, also known as the otic pit, is the first rudiment of the internal ear. It appears shortly after that of the eye, in the form of a patch of thickened ectoderm, the auditory plate, over the region of the hind-brain. The auditory plate becomes depressed and converted into the auditory pit (or otic pit).
A fold or lobe or pair of lobes of the body wall of a mollusk or brachiopod that in shell-bearing forms lines the shell and bears shell-secreting glands.
Within the shell is a fleshy layer of tissue called the mantle; there is a cavity (the mantle cavity) between the mantle and the body wall proper.
A muscle organ that is part of a mantle.
a balance sensory receptor present in some aquatic invertebrates[WP].
Exoskeleton or shell, including those of mollusks, turtles, insects and crustaceans.
A rigid covering that envelops an object.
A valve that is part of a vein.
Epithelium composed of secretory cells.
A vasculature that is part of a organ.
A head mesenchyme that develops_from a mesoderm.
A glandular epithelium that lines the stomach. The stomach's glandular epithelium is characterized by the presence of gastric glands.
Simple columnar epithelium that constitutes the secretory part of a gland. Examples: epithelium of stomach, luminal epithelium of lactiferous duct.[FMA]
A mucosa of stomach that is part of a stomach glandular region.
An epithelium that is part of a vestibular labyrinth.
Simple columnar epithelium made up of cells specialized to serve as sensory cells for the reception of external stimuli, as the sensory cells of the cochlea, vestibule, nasal mucosa, and tongue.
An epithelium that is part of a internal ear.

The vascular cord is the primordial vasculature that will develop into blood vessels by the process of tubulogenesis[GO]. The vascular cord is composed of angioblast or vascular endothelial cells in a solid linear mass called a cord. The cord then undergoes tubulogenesis to form the lumen of the vessels[ZFA].
Organism at the cleavage stage.
The collection of structures that form the extenal covering of the organism.
Ganglion which is located in the trunk.

label.value: mesenchyme derived from head neural crest

definition.value: Mesenchyme that develops_from a cranial neural crest.
Any collection of muscles that is part of an appendage.
A presumptive structure that has_potential_to_develop_into a neural plate.
A blood vessel that is part of a limb/fin.
A vasculature that is part of a limb/fin.
The space within an epithelial sphere.
A domain of columnar epithelium in an embryo that represents the early stage of the development of the epithelial component of a new anatomical structure.
Mesenchyme with little extracellular matrix.
epithelial layer of the retina, ciliary body, or iris composed of cells containing pigment granules.

Anatomical structure in which parts of two or more anatomical structures establish physical continuity with one another or intermingle their component parts. Examples: gastroesophageal junction, line alba, knee joint.[FMA]
The anteriormost subdivision of the body that includes the head, jaws, pharyngeal region and the neck (if present). In vertebrates this is the subdivision that includes the cervical vertebrae.
Musculature system of the pharyngeal and head regions.
An embryonic structure that is derived from the inner cell mass and lies above the hypoblast and gives rise to the three primary germ layers

an external organ of a male organism that is specialized to deliver sperm during copulation. Intromittent organs are found most often in terrestrial species, as most aquatic species fertilize their eggs externally, although there are exceptions[WP].
A head that is part of a embryo.
An organ part that is part of a stomach.
A gonad prior to differentiating into a definitive testis or ovary.
